As a Brit, I can tell you that the people regulating Ofcom are the tyrannical Conservative Party, many of whom support terrorism, cyberbully every non-Tory, and some are pedophiles.

Ofcom shouldn't regulate the Internet. What the Internet needs is worldwide regulation from the UN, because the Internet is worldwide and should be treated as such. Individual nations attempting to regulate the Internet is disastrous, because the Internet almost always has to follow, say for example, American laws ALL THE TIME, even when the person using the Internet has never been to America.

I call on the UN to take action and create ONE, SINGULAR REGULATORY BODY for the Internet. This way, we may have a more free and equal Internet for all.
